comments: Washington (CHA) turns to roll and incidental contact occurs with Bridges (BKN) as Bridges goes under the pick.
Williams (CHA) establishes himself in Johnson's (BKN) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Claxton (BKN) briefly places his hands against Williams' (CHA) body as the pick is set and slides his hands off immediately as Williams rolls towards the basket.
Bridges (BKN) extends his forearm into Rozier's (CHA) body, affecting his driving shot attempt.
Hayward (CHA) places his forearm to Bridges' (BKN) side and marginal contact occurs during Bridges' drive to the basket.
Finney-Smith (BKN) avoids stepping out of bounds while still in possession of the ball.
Rozier (CHA) moves alongside of Dinwiddie (BKN) and lightly brushes Dinwiddie's arm contesting his driving shot attempt.
Hayward (CHA) establishes himself in Bridges' (BKN) path and absorbs the contact.
Claxton (BKN) already has his arm extended moving along Rozier's (CHA) path and lightly brushes Rozier's arm prior to him entering his step back move.
Rozier (CHA) extends his leg out as part of his shooting motion and marginal contact occurs with Claxton (BKN) during the jump shot attempt.
Hayward (CHA) and Bridges (CHA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs coming off the screen.
Williams (CHA) legally contests Dinwiddie's (BKN) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Washington (CHA) reaches downwards at the ball and marginal contact occurs with Claxton's (BKN) leg during the shot attempt at the basket.
Hayward (CHA) establishes himself in Bridges's (BKN) path and absorbs the contact.
Dinwiddie (BKN) briefly grasps Williams' (CHA) arm as they come together during the pick and slides his hands off as Williams rolls towards the rim.
Finney-Smith (BKN) and Williams (CHA) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Claxton (BKN) reaches in for the ball and any contact with Williams' (CHA) arm occurs after the game clock expires.
